cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel ConvNet model for predicting 2D human body poses in an image. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the model is trained end-to-end and from scratch, with auxiliary losses incorporated to improve performance. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the model is able to learn and represent both the part appearances and the context of the part configuration. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the model is evaluated on benchmark datasets for human pose estimation in images. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the model uses a recurrent module that can be run iteratively to improve performance.
